{"id":"HmItUa","title":"Create REST API for Homespun","titleLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:39:03.5564218+00:00","titleModifiedBy":"nick-boey","description":"A REST API should be designed and implemented to allow programmatic access to the underlying functionality of Homespun. This will should simplify agentic access for testing backend functionality on live applications. The methods that are called by the API should be the same methods that are called by the application front end. It should be documented as a Swagger API.","descriptionLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:39:03.5564218+00:00","descriptionModifiedBy":"nick-boey","status":"Next","statusLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:39:03.5564218+00:00","statusModifiedBy":"nick-boey","type":"Feature","typeLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:39:03.5564218+00:00","typeModifiedBy":"nick-boey","linkedIssues":["KE7DaN"],"linkedIssuesLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:59:09.356322+00:00","linkedIssuesModifiedBy":"nick-boey","parentIssues":[],"parentIssuesLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:39:03.5564218+00:00","parentIssuesModifiedBy":"nick-boey","previousIssues":[],"previousIssuesLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:39:03.5564218+00:00","previousIssuesModifiedBy":"nick-boey","tags":[],"tagsLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:39:03.5564218+00:00","tagsModifiedBy":"nick-boey","questions":[],"questionsLastUpdate":"0001-01-01T00:00:00+00:00","createdBy":"nick-boey","createdByLastUpdate":"2026-01-24T05:54:44.2882736+00:00","lastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:59:09.356322+00:00","createdAt":"2026-01-24T05:54:44.2882736+00:00"}
{"id":"KE7DaN","title":"Add REST API with Swagger for backend testing","titleLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:57:51.4211891+00:00","titleModifiedBy":"nick-boey","description":"Implement a REST API layer to enable programmatic access and API-level testing of Homespun functionality.\n\n## Architecture\n- Keep Blazor components using @inject for direct service access (no change)\n- Add thin API controllers that call existing services\n- Add Swagger/OpenAPI documentation\n\n## API Endpoints\n\n### Projects\n- GET /api/projects - List all projects\n- GET /api/projects/{id} - Get project by ID\n- POST /api/projects - Create project\n- PUT /api/projects/{id} - Update project\n- DELETE /api/projects/{id} - Delete project\n\n### Pull Requests\n- GET /api/projects/{id}/pull-requests - List PRs for project\n- GET /api/pull-requests/{id} - Get PR by ID\n- POST /api/pull-requests - Create PR\n- PUT /api/pull-requests/{id} - Update PR\n- POST /api/projects/{id}/sync - Sync PRs from GitHub\n\n### Git Worktrees\n- GET /api/worktrees - List worktrees\n- POST /api/worktrees - Create worktree\n- DELETE /api/worktrees/{path} - Delete worktree\n\n### Claude Sessions\n- GET /api/sessions - List active sessions\n- GET /api/sessions/{id} - Get session details\n- POST /api/sessions - Start new session\n- POST /api/sessions/{id}/messages - Send message to session\n- DELETE /api/sessions/{id} - Stop session\n\n### Fleece Issues\n- GET /api/projects/{id}/issues - List issues for project\n- GET /api/issues/{id} - Get issue by ID\n- POST /api/issues - Create issue\n- PUT /api/issues/{id} - Update issue\n\n### Notifications\n- POST /api/notifications - Send notification (testing)\n\n## Files to Create\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| Features/Projects/Controllers/ProjectsController.cs | Projects REST API |\n| Features/PullRequests/Controllers/PullRequestsController.cs | PRs REST API |\n| Features/Git/Controllers/WorktreesController.cs | Worktrees REST API |\n| Features/ClaudeCode/Controllers/SessionsController.cs | Sessions REST API |\n| Features/Fleece/Controllers/IssuesController.cs | Issues REST API |\n\n## Files to Modify\n- Program.cs - Add Swagger, API explorer\n\n## Implementation Steps\n1. Add Swagger/OpenAPI to Program.cs\n2. Create ProjectsController (simplest, validates pattern)\n3. Implement remaining controllers\n\n## Verification\n- Navigate to /swagger and test each endpoint\n- Confirm Blazor components still work with @inject","descriptionLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:57:51.4211891+00:00","descriptionModifiedBy":"nick-boey","status":"Complete","statusLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T01:12:50.8599189+00:00","statusModifiedBy":"nick-boey","type":"Feature","typeLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:57:51.4211891+00:00","typeModifiedBy":"nick-boey","linkedIssues":[],"linkedIssuesLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:57:51.4211891+00:00","linkedIssuesModifiedBy":"nick-boey","parentIssues":[],"parentIssuesLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:57:51.4211891+00:00","parentIssuesModifiedBy":"nick-boey","previousIssues":[],"previousIssuesLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:57:51.4211891+00:00","previousIssuesModifiedBy":"nick-boey","tags":[],"tagsLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:57:51.4211891+00:00","tagsModifiedBy":"nick-boey","questions":[],"questionsLastUpdate":"0001-01-01T00:00:00+00:00","createdBy":"nick-boey","createdByLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:57:51.4211891+00:00","lastUpdate":"2026-01-26T01:12:50.8599189+00:00","createdAt":"2026-01-26T00:57:51.4211891+00:00"}
{"id":"jgc4Vz","title":"Add API integration tests","titleLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:12.5601094+00:00","titleModifiedBy":"nick-boey","description":"Create integration tests for the REST API endpoints to enable fast, stable testing of business logic.\n\n## Prerequisites\n- Depends on REST API implementation (issue KE7DaN)\n\n## Test Infrastructure\n\nCreate new test project: tests/Homespun.Api.Tests/\n- Use Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Testing for WebApplicationFactory\n- Configure test data store\n\n## Test Pattern\n\n\u0060\u0060\u0060csharp\npublic class ProjectsApiTests : IClassFixture\u003CWebApplicationFactory\u003CProgram\u003E\u003E\n{\n    private readonly HttpClient _client;\n\n    public ProjectsApiTests(WebApplicationFactory\u003CProgram\u003E factory)\n    {\n        _client = factory.WithWebHostBuilder(builder =\u003E\n        {\n            builder.ConfigureServices(services =\u003E\n            {\n                // Replace IDataStore with test implementation\n                services.AddSingleton\u003CIDataStore, TestDataStore\u003E();\n            });\n        }).CreateClient();\n    }\n\n    [Test]\n    public async Task GetProjects_ReturnsEmptyList_WhenNoProjects()\n    {\n        var response = await _client.GetAsync(\u0022/api/projects\u0022);\n        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();\n        var projects = await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync\u003CList\u003CProject\u003E\u003E();\n        Assert.That(projects, Is.Empty);\n    }\n}\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\n\n## Files to Create\n- tests/Homespun.Api.Tests/Homespun.Api.Tests.csproj\n- tests/Homespun.Api.Tests/ProjectsApiTests.cs\n- tests/Homespun.Api.Tests/PullRequestsApiTests.cs\n- tests/Homespun.Api.Tests/SessionsApiTests.cs\n- tests/Homespun.Api.Tests/IssuesApiTests.cs\n- tests/Homespun.Api.Tests/WorktreesApiTests.cs\n\n## Files to Modify\n- Homespun.sln - Add new test project\n\n## Verification\n- Run: dotnet test tests/Homespun.Api.Tests\n- All API endpoints should have test coverage","descriptionLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:12.5601094+00:00","descriptionModifiedBy":"nick-boey","status":"Complete","statusLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T01:16:51.3985015+00:00","statusModifiedBy":"nick-boey","type":"Feature","typeLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:12.5601094+00:00","typeModifiedBy":"nick-boey","linkedIssues":[],"linkedIssuesLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:12.5601094+00:00","linkedIssuesModifiedBy":"nick-boey","parentIssues":[],"parentIssuesLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:12.5601094+00:00","parentIssuesModifiedBy":"nick-boey","previousIssues":["KE7DaN"],"previousIssuesLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:12.5601094+00:00","previousIssuesModifiedBy":"nick-boey","tags":[],"tagsLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:12.5601094+00:00","tagsModifiedBy":"nick-boey","questions":[],"questionsLastUpdate":"0001-01-01T00:00:00+00:00","createdBy":"nick-boey","createdByLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:12.5601094+00:00","lastUpdate":"2026-01-26T01:16:51.3985015+00:00","createdAt":"2026-01-26T00:58:12.5601094+00:00"}
{"id":"UW4V9C","title":"Add bUnit component tests","titleLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:30.7413202+00:00","titleModifiedBy":"nick-boey","description":"Add bUnit testing for Blazor components to test rendering and component logic without a browser.\n\n## Overview\nbUnit enables testing Blazor components in isolation - fast execution, no browser needed, mocks services and verifies rendering.\n\n## Setup\n\nAdd bUnit package to existing test project:\n\u0060\u0060\u0060xml\n\u003CPackageReference Include=\u0022bunit\u0022 Version=\u00221.35.9\u0022 /\u003E\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\n\n## Test Structure\n\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\ntests/Homespun.Tests/\n\u251C\u2500\u2500 Components/\n\u2502   \u251C\u2500\u2500 ProjectDetailTests.cs\n\u2502   \u251C\u2500\u2500 PullRequestTreeTests.cs\n\u2502   \u251C\u2500\u2500 SessionChatTests.cs\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 ...\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\n\n## Test Pattern\n\n\u0060\u0060\u0060csharp\npublic class ProjectDetailTests : TestContext\n{\n    [Test]\n    public void ProjectDetail_DisplaysProjectName()\n    {\n        var mockProjectService = new Mock\u003CProjectService\u003E();\n        mockProjectService.Setup(s =\u003E s.GetByIdAsync(It.IsAny\u003Cstring\u003E()))\n            .ReturnsAsync(new Project { Id = \u00221\u0022, Name = \u0022Test Project\u0022 });\n\n        Services.AddSingleton(mockProjectService.Object);\n\n        var cut = RenderComponent\u003CProjectDetail\u003E(parameters =\u003E\n            parameters.Add(p =\u003E p.Id, \u00221\u0022));\n\n        cut.WaitForAssertion(() =\u003E\n            cut.Find(\u0022h1\u0022).TextContent.Should().Contain(\u0022Test Project\u0022));\n    }\n}\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\n\n## Components to Test\n- ProjectDetail - Project display and actions\n- PullRequestTree - PR hierarchy rendering\n- SessionChat - Claude session messaging UI\n- AgentManagementPanel - Agent status display\n- IssueList - Fleece issue display\n\n## Files to Modify\n- tests/Homespun.Tests/Homespun.Tests.csproj - Add bUnit package\n\n## Files to Create\n- tests/Homespun.Tests/Components/ProjectDetailTests.cs\n- tests/Homespun.Tests/Components/PullRequestTreeTests.cs\n- tests/Homespun.Tests/Components/SessionChatTests.cs\n- (additional component tests as needed)\n\n## Verification\n- Run: dotnet test tests/Homespun.Tests\n- All bUnit tests should pass","descriptionLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:30.7413202+00:00","descriptionModifiedBy":"nick-boey","status":"Complete","statusLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T01:21:10.8313749+00:00","statusModifiedBy":"nick-boey","type":"Feature","typeLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:30.7413202+00:00","typeModifiedBy":"nick-boey","linkedIssues":[],"linkedIssuesLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:30.7413202+00:00","linkedIssuesModifiedBy":"nick-boey","parentIssues":[],"parentIssuesLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:30.7413202+00:00","parentIssuesModifiedBy":"nick-boey","previousIssues":[],"previousIssuesLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:30.7413202+00:00","previousIssuesModifiedBy":"nick-boey","tags":[],"tagsLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:30.7413202+00:00","tagsModifiedBy":"nick-boey","questions":[],"questionsLastUpdate":"0001-01-01T00:00:00+00:00","createdBy":"nick-boey","createdByLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:30.7413202+00:00","lastUpdate":"2026-01-26T01:21:10.8313749+00:00","createdAt":"2026-01-26T00:58:30.7413202+00:00"}
{"id":"Gt9tAc","title":"Add Playwright E2E tests for critical journeys","titleLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:51.6944021+00:00","titleModifiedBy":"nick-boey","description":"Add selective Playwright end-to-end tests for critical user journeys to ensure the full application stack works correctly.\n\n## Overview\nPlaywright tests the entire application stack including UI rendering. Use sparingly - only for critical user journeys (5-10 tests).\n\n## Setup\n\nCreate new test project: tests/Homespun.E2E.Tests/\n- Add Microsoft.Playwright.NUnit package\n- Configure to start application before tests\n\n## Critical Journeys to Test\n\n1. Home page loads and displays projects list\n2. Create new project workflow\n3. View project detail with PR tree\n4. Start Claude session and send message\n5. GitHub sync completes successfully\n\n## Test Pattern\n\n\u0060\u0060\u0060csharp\n[Parallelizable(ParallelScope.Self)]\n[TestFixture]\npublic class CriticalJourneysTests : PageTest\n{\n    [Test]\n    public async Task HomePage_LoadsSuccessfully()\n    {\n        await Page.GotoAsync(\u0022https://localhost:5001\u0022);\n        await Expect(Page.Locator(\u0022h1\u0022)).ToContainTextAsync(\u0022Projects\u0022);\n    }\n\n    [Test]\n    public async Task CreateProject_AddsToList()\n    {\n        await Page.GotoAsync(\u0022https://localhost:5001\u0022);\n        await Page.ClickAsync(\u0022text=New Project\u0022);\n        await Page.FillAsync(\u0022input[name=name]\u0022, \u0022Test Project\u0022);\n        await Page.ClickAsync(\u0022text=Create\u0022);\n        await Expect(Page.Locator(\u0022text=Test Project\u0022)).ToBeVisibleAsync();\n    }\n}\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\n\n## Files to Create\n- tests/Homespun.E2E.Tests/Homespun.E2E.Tests.csproj\n- tests/Homespun.E2E.Tests/CriticalJourneysTests.cs\n\n## Files to Modify\n- Homespun.sln - Add new test project\n\n## Notes\n- Tests require running application\n- Slower than API/unit tests - use sparingly\n- May need to handle Blazor Server interactivity waits\n\n## Verification\n- Start app: dotnet run --project src/Homespun\n- Run: dotnet test tests/Homespun.E2E.Tests\n- All E2E tests should pass","descriptionLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:51.6944021+00:00","descriptionModifiedBy":"nick-boey","status":"Complete","statusLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T01:24:12.4135157+00:00","statusModifiedBy":"nick-boey","type":"Feature","typeLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:51.6944021+00:00","typeModifiedBy":"nick-boey","linkedIssues":[],"linkedIssuesLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:51.6944021+00:00","linkedIssuesModifiedBy":"nick-boey","parentIssues":[],"parentIssuesLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:51.6944021+00:00","parentIssuesModifiedBy":"nick-boey","previousIssues":[],"previousIssuesLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:51.6944021+00:00","previousIssuesModifiedBy":"nick-boey","tags":[],"tagsLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:51.6944021+00:00","tagsModifiedBy":"nick-boey","questions":[],"questionsLastUpdate":"0001-01-01T00:00:00+00:00","createdBy":"nick-boey","createdByLastUpdate":"2026-01-26T00:58:51.6944021+00:00","lastUpdate":"2026-01-26T01:24:12.4135157+00:00","createdAt":"2026-01-26T00:58:51.6944021+00:00"}
